  "texts": [
    "The danger of hallucinations permeates applications of LLMs for dementia care, including inaccurate information retrieval, inaccurate therapeutic processes, wrong summarization as a reading aid, or incorrect instructions when used as a navigation aid.",
    "Bias refers to tendencies in the model's responses that unfairly favor or disfavor certain groups or perspectives.",
    "This happens due to imbalances or prejudices in the training data, which often involves large amounts of uncurated text crawled from the internet (Naveed et al., 2023), or the model's learning process (Blodgett et al., 2020; Hovy and Prabhumoye, 2021; Ferrara, 2023; Field et al., 2023; Gallegos et al., 2023).",
    "Bias can manifest as stereotypes, underrepresentation of certain groups, or unfair treatment of specific topics (Birhane et al., 2021).",
    "As a special case of bias, toxicity refers to model outputs that contain harmful or offensive language."
  ],
